    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nSome servers support concept of `virtual documents` that are not real files but are generated on the fly when requested by client.\n\nSuch example is `source generation` for dotnet/roslyn.\n\nRecently roslyn team implemented support for standard lsp method to handle it (instead of using custom ones)\n- `workspace/textDocumentContent`\n- `workspace/textDocumentContent/refresh`\nLSP spec: https://microsoft.github.io/language-server-protocol/specifications/lsp/3.18/specification/#workspace_textDocumentContent\n\nHere is an attempt for implementing it for roslyn [`roslyn.nvim`](https://github.com/seblyng/roslyn.nvim/pull/355) plugin but as pointed by @tris203 it's better to implement it in core right away.\n\nAs mentioned also here https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/30908, implementation idea would be to register `BufReadCmd` autocmd for every scheme that server exposes in `server_capabilities.workspace.textDocumentContent.schemes`\n\nRoslyn issue: https://github.com/dotnet/roslyn/issues/80276\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nNeovim is able to open such virtual document (via references or go to definition for example) and keep it in sync with changes when lsp server will notify about it.\n\nSample from c#\n\n<img width=\"2524\" height=\"593\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/5886a189-34f1-4722-b19b-eaf51cd78243\" />",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
